# Issues to be fixed in the next version

The following issues have been found during tool usage and should be fixed one by one.
Use this file as a basis checklist and compile a prompt for each task to orchestrate the fixes. The code shall be changed incrementally.

* [ ] The theme is ugly. Dark background and white diagrams are not nice. There should be configureable themes:
  - dark
  - light
  - high contrast
  - dark-blue
  - dark-green
  Themes should not be hardcoded in the code, but loaded from a separate style file to make the codebase more readable.
* [ ] Loading the locations and metadata of a folder with many tracks takes very long - this information should be somhow cached;
    If possible, the tool should be responsive while the data is retrieved
* [ ] When differennt FIT files are selected and some have heart rate data and other don't, the average section is not correctly recomputed.
There is an average heart rate displayed, even if this is not possible because the selected FIT file does not contain this data.
* [ ] The tool should also support GPX files to make it more general-purpose.
* [ ] The select folder button should have a folder logo - otherwise it is hard to recognize
* [ ] The minor grid in the plot should be dashed instead of solid
* [ ] The last opened folder should be restored when the tool is started - this would be more convenient
* [ ] The statistics section should evaluate a fitness score based on the average heart rate and the average power - if both are available. The score should be computed for each activity separately. The score should be a number between 0 and 100, where 100 is the best possible score. 
